-- Bayer, Carrefour, Vodafone: European Equity Preview
-- B y   J o s e p h   C i o l l i
-- 2012-03-14T04:00:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-13/bayer-carrefour-vodafone-european-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
have unusual moves in  European (SXXP)  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  The  Stoxx Europe 600 Index (SXXP)  rose 1.8 percent to 269.56. The
 Stoxx 50 Index (SX5P)  increased 1.7 percent to 2,527.18. The  Euro Stoxx
50 Index (SX5E) , a benchmark measure for nations using the euro, gained
1.7 percent to 2,556.82.  Bayer AG (BAYN)  (BAYN GY): The largest German drugmaker won’t
yield to pressure from investors to sell its plastics
businesses, Boersen-Zeitung reported, citing an interview with
Chief Executive Officer Marijn Dekkers. The shares increased 1.2
percent to 55.63 euros.  Carrefour SA (CA)  : The world’s second-largest retailer
had its long-term issuer default rating and senior unsecured
rating cut to BBB from BBB+ by  Fitch Ratings , which cited the
company’s “weak” trading performance in 2011. The shares
gained 2.4 percent to 19.04 euros.  Vodafone Group Plc (VOD)  : The world’s largest mobile-
phone operator issued $1 billion of five-year, 1.625 percent
bonds. The shares rose 0.2 percent to 170.75 pence.  Voestalpine AG (VOE)  :  Austria ’s biggest steelmaker set
aside 205 million euros ($268 million) in reserves for risks
stemming from antitrust proceedings pertaining to its TSTG
Schienen Technik GmbH subsidiary, and said it will close the
unit by year-end, as it is no longer economically viable. The
shares increased 3 percent to $26.67.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Joseph Ciolli in New York at 
 jciolli@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
